column5: Water temps just below 60F. Bass are everywhere; from 5' to 20'. Southern shorelines with dark bottom or rocks seem to be holding them, as does any remaining green vegetation.
Thanks.  I'm heading close to Fenlon for some fishing!
i hope the water levels are a bit better,the lakes i was on 2 weeks ago are down up to 5-6 feet !!! ...but thanks for the info...cheers
Thanks for the update sd! Just leaving work, long day on the water tomorrow
Great update...got a couple beautiful spots on southern shorelines....will be checkin them out this weekend!
